<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian Speaks in UN Assembly on International Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier
and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen delivered a speech on the current
international situation as well as China's domestic development
this morning during the general debate of the United Nations
General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Qian, who is in New York to attend the 52nd session of the U.N.
General Assembly, also expounded China's positions on the reforms
of the world body.
</P>
<P>
He expressed appreciations of the efforts being made by U.N.
Secretary-General Kofi Annan in reviving and strengthening the
United Nations. Annan put forward a reform package in mid-July,
including 29 measures and 15 proposals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
