<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT September 24 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak completed his
three-day official visit to Moscow Wednesday that resulted in a
joint declaration with Russian president and documents on
cooperation in the political, economic, legal, investment and
other spheres.
</P>
<P>
The visit, the first by a Egyptian president to Russia since
its independence in 1991, is aimed at stimulating the bilateral
relations which had hard times in recent years, Itar-Tass said.
(Egypt-Russia-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Tokyo prosecutors Wednesday arrested Atsuo Miki,
former president of Yamaichi Securities Co., in connection with
the brokerage's alleged payoffs of some 79 million yen (660,000
U.S. dollars) to a corporate racketeer.
</P>
<P>
The Tokyo District Public Prosecutors Office suspects that Miki
approved illegal compensations to the suspected racketeer Ryuichi
Koike for securities trading losses, in violation of the
Commercials Code and the Securities and Exchange
Law. (Yamaichi-Arrest)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ALMA-ATA -- Visiting Chinese Premier Li Peng and Kazakh
President Nursultan Abishevich Nazarbayev signed here Wednesday a
supplementary border agreement between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders inked the agreement after talks at the
president's complex.
</P>
<P>
They also witnessed the signing of an agreement between the two
governments on a cooperative project of petroleum and natural gas
by Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing and Kazakh Deputy Prime
Minister and Minister of Economy and Trade Umirzak Estaevich
Shukeev. (Kazakhstan-China-Border-Pact)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korean President Kim Young-sam formally resigned
as head of the ruling New Korea Party (NKP) today, paving the way
for party presidential candidate Lee Hoi-chang to take the helm of
the troubled party.
</P>
<P>
Kim submitted his resignation to the NKP head office via his
senior secretary for political affairs Cho Hong-rae this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Lee is expected to become party leader in a national convention
to be held September 30, with Kim as an honorary president of the
party. (SKorea-Kim Young-sam)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia has already crossed the "main line," with a
free economy taking its root and a reversion to the past
impossible, said Russian President Boris Yeltsin here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Russian Federation Council, Yeltsin said
Russia's industrial downturn has stopped and production increase
has continued this year, reported the Itar-Tass news agency.
(Russia-Yeltsin-Address)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ALGIERS -- The Islamic Salvation Army (AIS), the armed wing of
the outlawed Islamic Salvation Front (FIS) of Algeria, Wednesday
announced a ceasefire with the government from October 1,
according to a communique by the armed group.
</P>
<P>
In the communique, which was signed by AIS National Emir Madani
Mezerag on September 21 and faxed to Agence France-Presse (AFP)
Bonn bureau today, AIS called on other armed Islamic groups in
Algeria "attached to Islam and the nation" to follow suit.
(Algeria-Ceasefire) 
</P>
</TEXT>
