<HEADLINE> Nepalese Party Congratulates Jiang on Re-election, Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Madhav Kumar Nepal, general
secretary of the Communist Party of Nepal (Unified
Marxist-Leninist), has congratulated Jiang Zemin on his
re-election as general secretary of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
Madhav Kumar Nepal, in his message to Jiang on Sunday, also
congratulated the successful conclusion of the 15th National
Congress of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
He was happy to learn about the important decisions made by the
Congress regarding the acceleration of economic reform, the drive
against corruption and malpractices and the building of a strong
and civilized socialist China.
</P>
<P>
"It will be a great contribution to socialism, world peace and
civilization," he said. 
</P>
