<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian Speaks on World Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier
Qian Qichen today called on the international community to help
stabilize the world financial market and ensure a steady economic
growth of the developing countries.
</P>
<P>
Qian, also minister of foreign affairs, made the call in his
speech at the 52nd session of the General Assembly here this
morning.
</P>
<P>
In the past year, the overall situation of the world economy
has been good, he said. Economic links and mutual penetration
among countries and regions are on the constant increase.
International cooperation should be given a fresh evaluation of
its importance with a view to making it broader, closer and more
fruitful, said Qian.
</P>
<P>
Developing countries are most vulnerable to the impact of
adverse environment because of their weak economic foundation, he
said.
</P>
<P>
"We hope the international community, developed countries in
particular, will honor their pledges of providing funds and
transferring technology to the developing countries so as to
translate the declaration of partnership into real action," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He also called the attention of the member states to many
"trans-boundary issues" such as poverty, unemployment, refugees,
drugs and crime, which, he said, need to be addressed through
consultation by the international community.
</P>
<P>
"Work of the United Nations in the social field needs to be
strengthened," he said.
</P>
<P>
The international community should get down to practical work,
the first of which is to help developing countries with their most
urgent difficulties, he said. China will continue to support the
United Nations in its work in the social field and make greater
contribution to social progress around the world, he added
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
