<HEADLINE> Two U.N. Staff Killed in Southeast Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations World
Food Program (WFP) today announced that its two staff members had
been shot dead and another staff escaped unwounded in Ethiopia's
Central Ogaden region.
</P>
<P>
A news release issued here today said three WFP personnel were
travelling late Friday afternoon from Kebre Dehar to Jigiga after
a field mission when their vehicle was stopped by armed men at a
place, 55 kilometers south of Degeh Bur.
</P>
<P>
After the gunmen led them away from their vehicle, one of the
three men managed to escape and fled to the nearby town of Birkot
where he reported the incident to the local authorities.
</P>
<P>
The release noted that security teams were immediately
dispatched to the place where they found no trace of the two WFP
staff and located only the vehicle which had been vandalized.
</P>
<P>
Catherine Bertini, WFP Executive Director, condemned the
brutal incident, saying the number of attacks on humanitarian
workers worldwide had been on the rise, making it increasingly
difficult to deliver relief assistance.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the area of Central Ogaden in Ethiopia
had been increasingly insecure over recent months due to tensions
on the border region between Somalia and Ethiopia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
