<HEADLINE> UN Takes No Further Action Against UNOMIG Commander </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
took no further action against the commander of the U.N. Observer
Mission on Georgia (UNOMIG) for paying a ransom to secure the
release of two hostages, U.N. spokesman Fred Eckhard said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Major-General Harun Ar-Rashisd of Bangladesh was recalled to
the U.N. Headquarters over the weekend to explain why a total of
7,000 U.S. dollars was paid to obtain the release of a U.N.
military observer and a local interpreter taken hostages by
unknown elements days ago.
</P>
<P>
