reaffirmed to him the policy of not paying ransom and not
negotiating over hostages, and hearing his complete account of how
things happened, we felt there were mitigating circumstances."
</P>
<P>
"We are very concerned about the precedent, which is why we
called him here," added the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
A total of 115 U.N. military observers are stationed in the
country, where a large Russian-led peacekeeping force fielded by
the Commonwealth of Independent States has been patrolling a
buffer zone of Georgia and the breakaway region of Abkhazia.
</P>
