<HEADLINE> S. Leonean Junta's Talks Offer Refuted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The offer of Sierra Leone's
military junta to hold talks with ousted President Ahmed Tejan Kabbah
on the current political impasse in the country was refuted today.
</P>
<P>
A senior official of Kabbah's government, Desmond Luke, said the
offer only indicated the junta's attempt to "play for time" for
continued stay in power.
</P>
<P>
The official, who was negotiating with the rebel Revolutionary
United Front (RUF) at the time of the coup on May 25 which overthrew
the Kabbah administration, has been in Conakry, capital of neighboring
Guinea, with the ousted president.
</P>
<P>
"They (the junta) have trying to play for time, purely waste time
in order to continue killing, stealing, looting people's property,"
Cluke said, quoted by the British Broadcasting Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The junta reportedly asked for talks with President Conte in early
August to resume peace negotiations that failed in Abijan, Cote
d'Ivoire in July after the junta announced to stay in power until
2001.
</P>
<P>
The international community has urged the junta to return power to
Kabbah without delay and the west African peacekeeping force has
enforced economic embargo on the country for this purpose.
</P>
<P>
Under the pressure, the junta confirmed Tuesday that military
leader Major Johnny Paul Koroma wanted a peaceful solution to the
country's crisis through talks with Kabbah and RUF leader Foday
Sankoh.
</P>
<P>
But Luke had no trust in the junta, saying that the military
government was not serious about any negotiations for an immediate
handover as required by the international community.
</P>
<P>
"They indicated twice that they wanted to talk with President
Lansana Conte (of Guinea)...but they have not been earnest in the
least right at the start," he said.
</P>
<P>
The official said the junta, which has put Sierra Leone back for
50 years, only wanted to continue to run the country instead of
return power to the ousted civilian government.  
</P>
</TEXT>
