<HEADLINE> Heavy Fighting Continuing in Brazzaville </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, September 24 (Xinhua) --Fighting goes on today in the
Congolese capital Brazzaville and it has become the center of
heavy artillery battles.
</P>
<P>
People in the capital fear that the situation may completely
get out of control, said reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Some 4000 people are reported to have been killed since
fighting started in June when the Congolese government forces
tried to disarm militiamen loyal to former President Sassou
Nguesso.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of Congolese citizens have fled the country since
several peace talks aimed at ending the civil war in the country
failed.
</P>
<P>
As fighting continues in the capital, police in Kinshsa, the
capital of the neighboring Democratic Republic of Congo, have
tightened control of those refugees crossing the Congo River and
ordered refugees from Brazzaville to register with authorities.
</P>
<P>
Police also closed three Congo River crossing points.
</P>
<P>
Reports said a United Nations refugee agency camp held at
least 20,000 refugees from the fighting in Brazzaville. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
