<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Qian Qichen, Chinese
vice-premier and foreign minister, told his Dutch counterpart,
Hans Van Mierlo, today that China hopes to develop relations with
the European Union countries including the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands is one of China's major trade partners in
Western Europe. Both sides not only could develop trade relations
on the basis of equality and mutual benefit, but also should
conduct exchanges on the basis of mutual respect, said Qian in
meeting with Mierlo at the U.N. headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders are attending the 52nd session of the United
Nations General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Qian said, though differences exist on some questions, the two
countries could develop their relations healthily and normally, so
long as they respect each other and show their good faith.
</P>
<P>
Mierlo agreed with Qian on the bilateral relations. He said
that the two countries have a long history of exchange and the
Dutch Chinese have made important contributions to the development
of his country.
</P>
<P>
He hoped the two countries to continue exchanges in various
fields and on different levels with equal footing. 
</P>
