<HEADLINE> Nine to Run for Cameroon's Presidential Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Officials in the Ministry of
Territorial Administration of Cameroon said today that the
ministry has selected nine candidates to run for the October 12
presidential elections in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to the final list of candidates published yesterday
by the ministry, 10 candidates had complete files and were
retained by the ministry to take part in the election.
</P>
<P>
Officials in the ministry revealed that one candidates,
Victorin Hameni Bieleu, the Chairman of the Cameroon Democratic
Force Union (UFDC) withdrew his candidature yesterday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The files of seven other candidates were rejected by the
ministry for the lack of complete files.
</P>
<P>
According to today's Cameroon Tribune, three of the rejected
candidates have appealed to the Supreme Court acting in place of
the constitutional council.
</P>
<P>
They are Tchoumba Ngouankeu Issac of the Cameroun People's
Union (UPC); Onana Nouma Marius (independent candidate), and
Ekane Anicet of the African Movement for the New Independence and
Democracy (Manidem).
</P>
<P>
The appeal cases are in accordance with the law related to the
election of the president. The law requires that such complains
be made within two days following the publication of the list of
candidates. 
</P>
