<HEADLINE> S.Korean President Proposes Educational Camp for APEC Youth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, September 25 (Xinhua) -- South Korean President Kim
Young-sam proposed today that the Asia-Pacific region inaugurate a
"youth skill camp" to promote youth education and training with a
view to preparing them for the next century.
</P>
<P>
He make the proposal while welcoming delegates attending the
Second APEC (Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation) Ministerial
Meeting on Human Resources Development (HRD) which opened here.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the two-day APEC meeting is "The Strategy for HRD
Under a New Environment and Challenges."
</P>
<P>
Kim said that "the camp will provide a valuable opportunity for
all member economies to exchange information with each other on
youth education and training."
</P>
<P>
"In particular, we must all take great interest in the
education and training of youth, the mainstay of future society in
the area of information and the latest technology," he added.
</P>
<P>
Kim said that his country has been making various efforts to
support the development of human resources in APEC member
economies.
</P>
<P>
The President also mentioned that he proposed the launching of
an APEC Industrial and Technical Training Program for Human
Resources Development at last year's APEC summit in the
Philippines, for which South Korea is now working out details.
</P>
<P>
"The Republic of Korea intends to spearhead efforts to expand
education and training for human resources development in the
region," Kim said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
