<HEADLINE> Religious Leaders on Party National Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- China's religious leaders
praised the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China
today and gave their support to the newly elected Central
Committee with General Secretary Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting of leaders from various religions, Zhao Puchu,
vice chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) and chairman of the
Buddhist Association of China, said that Jiang Zemin spoke of
holding the banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory high, which will serve
as a guideline for building socialism with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Li Dezhu, deputy head of the United Front Work Department of
the CPC, presided over the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Ding Guangxun, honorary chairman of the Three-Self Patriotic
Movement Committee for Protecting the Churches of China and the
China Christian Council, said that all of the great changes in
China's religions in the past several years can be attributed to
the application of Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
An Shiwei, chairman of the Islamic Association of China, said
that Muslims will hold the banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory high and
fulfil the tasks put down by the Party Congress.
</P>
<P>
The Party Congress was also praised by Fu Tieshan, vice
chairman of Chinese Catholic Bishops College, and Luo Guanzong,
honorary chairman of Three-Self Patriotic Movement Committee for
Protecting the Churches of China.
</P>
<P>
Xie Zongxin, executive vice-chairman of the China Taoist
Association, said that the development of Taoism, a native
religion of China, should be in accordance with socialist society
and should contribute to the country's reunification and socialist
construction.

