<HEADLINE> Cypriot Police Have Largest Drug Haul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Cypriot police have seized
more than 7,000 grams of drugs in the country's largest-ever haul
and arrested four youths in connection, Cyprus News Agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Operating on a tip-off, police arrested Nicos Nikolaou, 20,
Wednesday night on arrival at Larnaca airport from the Netherlands
after finding 6,496 grams of marijuana and 1,148 grams of cannabis
resin in his suitcase.
</P>
<P>
Nikolaou then named three accomplices, leading to the other
arrests.
</P>
<P>
The police are further investigating the case. 
