<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Drafting Process of 15th Party Congress Report (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
During the meeting, Jiang elaborated on the historic
significance of the 15th Party National Congress, and reviewed the
development of the Chinese nation over the past 100-plus years,
especially the 50 years since the founding of the People's
Republic.
</P>
<P>
Since the Third Plenum of the 11th CPC Central Committee, he
said, the CPC had convened three national congresses, supplying
theoretical answers to a number of major issues of how to build
socialism in China.
</P>
<P>
He said, "We have built up Deng Xiaoping Theory on building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, formulated our Party's
basic line of taking economic construction as the central task
while adhering to the Four Cardinal Principles and upholding the
reform and the opening-up policy, set the objectives for
establishing a socialist market economic structure and formulated
the three-phase strategy for achieving modernization."
</P>
<P>
The report should review the major events of the past century,
particularly the five years since the 14th Party National
Congress, and look at the first 50 years of the next century, and
draw a blueprint for China's economic and social development by
the year 2049, the 100th anniversary of the founding of New China,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He declared his position on many issues including holding high
the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory, the basic line and
program for the primary stage of socialism, on economic, political,
cultural and diplomatic development, reunification of the
motherland and the CPC in the new period.
</P>
<P>
He urged the writers of the report to conscientiously study
Marxism-Leninism, Mao Zedong Thought and Deng Xiaoping Theory and
stick to the principle of emancipating the mind, seeking truth from
facts and making bold explorations under correct theoretical
guidance.
</P>
<P>
The 10-month drafting process was carried out under the direct
leadership of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of
the CPC Central Committee. Jiang always attached great importance to
the work and offered suggestions on much of the material to be
included.
</P>
<P>
In a May 29 speech at the graduation ceremony of the Party
School of the CPC Central Committee, attended by ministry-level
officials, Jiang explained the four main ideas of the report to
the 15th National Party Congress, stressing the issue of following
Deng Xiaoping Theory is of utmost importance as it represents
China's political orientation and image.
</P>
<P>
The writers of the report made revisions to their work
based on Jiang's May speech.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970925.0094 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
