<HEADLINE> China Cracking Down On Drug "Ice" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 25 (Xinhua) -- China is planning some strong
measures to deal with crimes involving the drug "ice", and to curb
sales of the drug.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting on crimes related to the drug held in this
southeastern Chinese city today, government public security,
transportation and medical officials called for increased
co-operation in controlling the raw materials used to manufacture
"ice", and for increased study and information on crimes related
to it.
</P>
<P>
In spite of the relatively small number of cases so far and the
small number of addicts and because of its relatively late
development in China, the potentially large markets in neighboring
countries and regions and the extremely high profits from the drug
may mean an increase in the number of crimes in the country in
future, the officials warned.
</P>
<P>
Increased efforts should be made to curb the growth of the
drug, and public awareness should be increased, the officials at
the meeting stressed.
</P>
<P>
They recommended that the experience gained by Guangdong and
Fujian provinces be used to help the rest of the country in the
fight against the drug-related crimes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
