<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Drafting Process of 15th Party Congress Report (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The process of drafting the report is a one of carrying out the
Party's fine tradition of inner Party democracy.
</P>
<P>
In the course of drafting, the Standing Committee of the
Political bureau of the CPC Central Committee held three meetings
to discuss the draft report. Finally, the central leading body had
an identical view on the major points of view of the report.
</P>
<P>
The draft report was printed and distributed to 135 work units
at central and local levels for soliciting their opinions based on
a decision made by the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee on July 10, this year.
</P>
<P>
The draft report was discussed by 4,000 people including
members of the 14th CPC Central Committee and of the Central
Commission for Discipline Inspection, leading officials of central
government departments, senior officers of military areas command,
leaders of non-governmental organizations, delegates to the 15th
National Congress and veteran Party members.
</P>
<P>
The CPC Central Committee also entrusted its United Front Work
Department to solicit opinions of non-communist parties, leading
officials of the All-China Federation of Industry and commerce and
persons without party affiliations.
</P>
<P>
Based on opinions from all social sectors, the drafting group
made more than 800 revisions to the report, shortening the length
of the report to 30,000 Chinese characters.
</P>
<P>
Then, the draft report was submitted to the Seventh Plenum of
the 14th CPC Central Committee for examination and approval on
September 6. The three-day Plenum approved the report after making
some revisions and decided to submit it to the 15th National Party
Congress for examination.
</P>
<P>
The draft report was revised for nine times before it was
presented to delegates to the 15th Party Congress. It was the
outcome of collective wisdom of the whole Party and represents the
common desire of people of all ethnic groups in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
