<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Loans to Four Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) approved here today a total of six loans to India,
Kyrgyzstan, Mongolia and Sri Lanka for various projects.
</P>
<P>
The ADB said in a statement that nearly 2 million Indians,
mostly from low-income groups, will have access to affordable
housing finance for the first time through three ADB loans
totaling 300 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The viability of enterprises in Kyrgyzstan will be enhanced
with the approval of a 40 million-U.S.-dollar loan, the bank's
first program on corporate governance, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
To help build a more reliable and efficient heating system for
the residents of Ulan Bator, the coldest capital in the world, the
bank also agreed to lend Mongolia 40 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, the ADB also decided to provide 20 million
dollars to help Sri Lanka increase land productivity and make farm
enterprises more profitable.  
</P>
