approved legislation today restricting the rights and activities
of minority religions, brushing aside Western objections and
sending the bill to President Boris Yeltsin. The U.S. Senate has
threatened to cut off U.S. aid to Russia if the bill becomes law.
</P>
<P>
-- Another brokerage powerhouse was born on Wall Street
Wednesday when Travelers Group announced it will acquire Salomon
Inc. and merge it with its Smith Barney unit, creating the
nation's second largest investment bank.
</P>
<P>
The wall Street Journal
</P>
<P>
-- The U.S. and Japan extended "open skies" negotiations into
next month after failing to agree on the details of a tentative
pact for U.S. airlines seeking new routes to Japan.
</P>
