<HEADLINE> Non-Communist Parties on 15th Party National Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- China's eight non-Communist
parties and the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce
have expressed support for the resolutions of the 15th National
Congress of Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
At a meeting of the Central Committee of the Revolutionary
Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang, Chairwoman He Luli said that
the most significant achievement of the Party Congress was the
decision to high high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping
Theory. The Committee should co-operate closely with the CPC in
invigorating the Chinese nation, she said, and make a contribution
to China's reunification in accordance with the "one country, two
systems" principle.
</P>
<P>
Ding Shisun, chairman of the Democratic League, said at a
senior league official meeting that, by holding the banner of Deng
Xiaoping Theory high, the CPC will make China a prosperous,
democratic and highly civilized socialist country in next century.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Siwei, chairman of the China Democratic National
Construction Association, told a meeting that General Secretary
Jiang Zemin stated that China will develop an economy with the
public-owned sector as the mainstay and common growth of other
sectors. This will enable the association to make full use of
its place in the economy.
</P>
<P>
The highlight of the CPC Congress also received high marks from
the China Association for Promoting Democracy, the China Peasants
and Workers Democratic Party, the China Zhi Gong Party, the Jiusan
Society, and the Taiwan Democratic Self-Government League.
</P>
<P>
Wang Guangying, honorary chairman of the All-China Federation
of Industry and Commerce, said that the highlight of the Party
Congress covers Deng Xiaoping Theory, the theory of socialism at a
primary stage, and taking economic development as the country's
central task. 
