<HEADLINE> EU Industrial Production Up in First Half 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 25 (Xinhua) -- European Union (EU)
industrial production rose by 1.4 percent in the first half of
this year, EU's statistic arm Eurostat reported today.
</P>
<P>
Leading the increase was Finland with 2.6 percent while
Germany, Spain, Italy and Sweden all scored above-EU average
growth, at 2.0, 1.7, 1.7 and 1.4 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
With an increase of 0.4 percent, Greece was at the bottom of
the 13 EU member states that have contributed data towards the
Eurostat report.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat said that the 15-nation union is now in a position to
register comparable growth to the United States and Japan, whose
respective second-quarter industrial production this year rose by
1.0 percent and 1.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
EU-wide first-quarter growth was 1.0 percent, as against the
growth of 0.6 percent in the third and fourth quarters of last
year.
</P>
<P>
The statistic bureau attributed the recovery to intermediate
goods that rose by 2.0 percent while capital goods and consumer
durables both increased by 1.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Consumer non-durables registered zero growth for the same
period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
