<HEADLINE> Vintage Cars Arrive in New Delhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 25 (Xinhua) -- About 90 vintage and
classic cars rolled into New Delhi Thursday in a rally that began
in Beijing and heads for Paris.
</P>
<P>
The automobiles, dating back to 1907 and boasting famous names
like Allard, Bentley, Mercedes Benz, Citroen, Deuvet, Morris, Ford
and Rolls Royce, left Beijing on September 6, travelling through
Nepal to India.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 drivers had started out from China on the
16,000-kilometer rally to France.
</P>
<P>
The event, which replicates a rally undertaken in 1907, is due
to finish in Paris on October 18.
</P>
<P>
Dutchman Johannes van der Laan was the first to enter Delhi. He
drove a 1958 Citroen 2CV. He was followed by R.C. Jessen of
Denmark on a 1924 Bentley sports car. 
