<HEADLINE> Xiangxi Tujia-Miao Autonomous Prefecture Marks 40th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Some 2.5 million people in
the Xiangxi Tujia-Miao Autonomous Prefecture in central China's
Hunan Province joined in celebrations today to mark the
prefecture's 40th anniversary.
</P>
<P>
State Council representatives and senior Hunan provincial
officials attended celebrations held in Jishou, capital of the
autonomous prefecture.
</P>
<P>
The Tujia and Miao ethnic groups live in communities
distributed throughout southwest China, with the majority living
in Hunan and Yunnan provinces.
</P>
<P>
Xiangxi prefecture's agricultural output has doubled over the
past four decades, with the prefecture forming n specialized
industrial sector centered on the production of chemicals,
building materials, tobacco and textiles.
</P>
<P>
The 1996 per capita earning of the prefecture's urban residents
hit 4,459 yuan, with the figure for farmers reaching 968 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The prefecture's poverty-stricken population has dropped
dramatically from 1.56 million in the early 1980s to around
350,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
