<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Releases 46 Iraqi POWs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Iran today unilaterally
released 46 Iraqi prisoners of war (POWs) in a bid to show
its goodwill toward its former enemy, Iran's official news agency
IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Brigadier General Abdullah Najafi, head of Iranian commission
in charge of POWs, said at the releasing ceremony that this
unilateral move is carried out in the light of Iran's
humanitarianism and Islamism and it is the decision of Ali
Khamenei, supreme leader and commander-in-chief of Iran's armed
forces.
</P>
<P>
Iran took such humanitarian measures many times in the past, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Najafi said that the number of Iraqi POWs released by Iran was
9,650 more than that of Iranian POWs released by the Iraqi regime,
expressing regret that the Iraqi government had not reciprocated
Iran's humanitarian measures.
</P>
<P>
"Not even a single Iranian POW had been released by the Iraqi
regime in the past five years," Najafi was quoted by IRNA as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi regime is holding Iranian POWS for political
purposes, he noted, adding that this practice run against
international laws.
</P>
<P>
Some 75,000 POWs have been exchanged since the end of the
Iran-Iraq war in 1988. But Iran has claimed that Iraq still holds
more than 5,000 Iranian POWs according to the documents it has.
However, Iraq has also stated that Iran still keeps some 20,000 Iraqi
POWs while rejecting the Iranian claim.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has said that it released all the Iranian POWs in 1990
and repatriated them to Iran under the supervision of the
international committee of the Red Cross.
</P>
<P>
Exchange of POWs and the remains of the missing soldiers during
the 1980-88 war between the two countries are still main obstacles
to the normalization of bilateral relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970925.0119 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China-US Hotline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- China and the United States
are discussing the possibility of opening a direct
telecommunications hotline linking leaders of the two nations.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at today's regularly scheduled press conference,
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Shen Guofang said that maintaining
contact and dialogue between the leaders of the two countries will
help deepen understanding between the two sides and facilitate the
the development of improved bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Shen noted that the two countries are engaged in wide-ranging
dialogues in many areas, including the economic, trade and and
political sectors.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that as two big countries, China and the United
States bear major responsibility for maintaining peace and
stability in the Asia-Pacific Region and the world as a whole. He
noted that certain disagreements exist between the two countries
due to different values, social systems, levels of economic growth
and cultural heritages.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, the Chinese side has always believed that the
common ground and interests shared by the two countries are far
more significant than differences.
</P>
<P>
The turn of the century is rapidly approaching and the two
countries should develop a sound, healthy, cooperative and
mutually beneficial relationship.
</P>
<P>
Shen pointed out that the relationship is in no way aimed at a
third country. It is not a relationship of alliance, said Shen.
</P>
<P>
He said it will be a new and solid bilateral relationship which
will ensure that disagreements can be resolved through friendly
negotiations and dialog.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out both sides recognize the vital importance and
significance of bilateral relations, and are fully cognizant of
the huge common ground they share.
</P>
<P>
Shen said that exchange visits by leaders of the two nations
will greatly enhance the healthy development of bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the Taiwan issue is a key to Sino-US
relations, and he noted that major obstacles hindering the
expansion of bilateral relations can be attributed to the issue.
</P>
<P>
Shen said that bilateral relations will continuously improve
and expand so long as the United States strictly abides by the
principles of the three joint communiques between the two
countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
