<HEADLINE> S. Africa, Mozambique to Be Linked by Train </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 25 (Xinhua) -- A new passenger train
will start running from South Africa through Swaziland to
Mozambique on November 1, Swaziland Railway Company Chief
Executive Officer Gideon Mahlalela said in Mbabane today.
</P>
<P>
Mahlalela said the train will operate between Durban, a port
city in South Africa, and Maputo, the capital of Mozambique via
eastern Swaziland.
</P>
<P>
Normal immigration and customs formalities will be conducted
at the points of entry and exit between South Africa and
Swaziland at Gollela and at Goba on the Swaziland/Mozambique
border, east of the Lomahasha border post.
</P>
<P>
Mpaka Railway Station in northeastern Swaziland will be
upgraded and will be the country's main station, Mahlalela said.
