<HEADLINE> Chirac Leaves on State Visit to Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 25 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
left here today on a three-day state visit to Russia, said the
Elysee Presidential Palace.
</P>
<P>
Chirac will hold talks with Russian President Boris Yeltsin
this afternoon and will make two speeches in Moscow and
Saint-Petersburg.
</P>
<P>
This is Chirac's second visit to Russia this year. He paid a
brief visit to Moscow in early February during which he discussed
with Yeltsin the signing of a charter on bilateral relations
between Russia and NATO.
</P>
<P>
Chirac will focus his talks with Russian leaders on the
development of French-Russian economic relations, which is marked
by a 10 billion franc (1.6 billion U.S. dollar) annual trade
deficit registered by France because of its purchase of Russian
gas.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will also discuss Russia's structural reform, its
full return to the international scenery and development of
relations between Russia and NATO.
</P>
<P>
Chirac will reaffirm France's stand that the three Baltic
states of Lithuania, Latvia and Estonia should not be admitted
into NATO.
</P>
<P>
He is also expected to meet with leader of the Russian
Communist Party Gennady Zyuganov and Alexander Shokhine, chief of
the presidential party, Our Home Russia. 
</P>
