<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. African, German Leaders to Meet Over Arms Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 25 (Xinhua) -- South African Deputy
President Thabo Mbeki will meet German Chancellor Helmut Kohl
next week to formalize establishment of the SA-German bi-national
commission, local daily Business Day reported today.
</P>
<P>
The proposed commission would pave a way for German leaders to
lobby South Africa about buying an arms package thought to be
worth more than 2.1 billion U.S. Dollars, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The package will include corvettes, jet trainers and
helicopters and matches in size similar to those offered from
British and French arms manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
Apart from his meeting with Kohl, Mbeki will meet German
Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel. He will also meet business
representatives, diplomatic sources said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Mbeki is scheduled to visit Nigeria soon, but no
exact date of the visit has been fixed yet, they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
