<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientists Discuss Jiang Zemin's Report  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have
pledged to hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping theory and
strive for the basic accomplishment of modernization by the middle
of the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The scientists made their pledge today during a meeting on the
report Jiang delivered during the 15th National Party Congress.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was jointly sponsored by six science and technology
departments, including the State Science and Technology Commission
(SSTC), the Commission of Science, Technology and Industry for
National Defense, the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS), and the
Chinese Academy of Engineering (CAE).
</P>
<P>
SSTC Minister Song Jian said the national Party congress
introduced the principle that the promotion of science and
technology is a key factor for economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's report pointed to the fact that Chinese scientists and
technicians, as well as people from the circle have learned their
responsibilities and historic mission, Song said.
</P>
<P>
Wang Daheng, an academician with both the CAS and the CAE, said
Jiang's report outlined the action program for China's science and
technology development.
</P>
<P>
The most important task is to adhere to the Party's leadership
and following the correct road for building socialism, and the
Party has clearly defined the correct path, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed out that Jiang Zemin has paid great attention
to basic scientific research which is regarded as the theoretical
basis for solving wide-ranging problems.
</P>
<P>
Ba Denian, president of the Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences
said that the study of Jiang's report has helped emancipated the
minds of scientists.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
