<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientists Discuss Jiang Zemin's Report   (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He called for recognition of China's most excellent scientists
and for the re-establishment of scientific research institutions
in order to quickly narrow the scientific development gap between
China and developed countries.
</P>
<P>
Wang Xuan, director of the Beijing University Computer Research
Institute, voiced his total agreement with Jiang's contention that
realizing diversified forms of public ownership is fully possible.
</P>
<P>
He said that further understanding public ownership will
promote efforts to upgrade state-owned enterprises and
hasten the establishment of modern regulations for enterprises.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Beijing University Founder Group Corp., a
share-holding company attached to Beijing University, has been
listed on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange since 1995, and that its
market value has soared from one billion yuan (12 million US
dollars) to over five billion yuan (about 600 million dollars) in
less then two years.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that Beijing University is the major
stockholder in the company, with substantial shares also held by
businessmen from Japan, the United States and Great Britain.
</P>
<P>
Beijing University operates several share-holding companies
which provide substantial funding for its research and teaching
programs, Wang noted. 
</P>
