<HEADLINE> Share Price Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Share prices rose on the
Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index
surged by 20.58 points to close at 1921.09 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 186.74 million units, valued
at 429.06 million Singapore dollars (about 284.15 million U.S.
dollars). Advances outnumbered declines by 186 to 145, while 277
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Rekapac was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 8.09 million units. It was followed by the Singapore
Telecom which had 7.84 million shares traded. RHB Capital
Warrant99 was next with 6.87 million units changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it jumped by 3.6 dollars to finish at 37.6 Singapore
dollars. The Singapore Airlines (SIA) Foreign and Venture rose by
70 cents each to end at 12.4 and 7.2 Singapore dollars
respectively. Venture Warrant9907 increased by 60 cents to close
at 5.9 dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Development Bank of Singapore (DBS)
Foreign was the biggest loser as it declined by 80 cents to end at
14.6 Singapore dollars. Ber Land fell by 71 cents to close at 2.14
dollars, while the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign finished
30 cents lower at 20.8 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
