<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Launches Communication Satellite </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Space Force
successfully launched a communication satellite from the Plesetsk
space center in the Arkhangelsk region today, the Itar-Tass news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Space Force press center was quoted as saying that
the Molnia 1T satellite has been put into orbit by a Molnia M
four-stage booster manufactured by the Progress rocket-space
center in Samara.
</P>
<P>
The satellite, which will ensure long-distance telephone
communications, was made by the research center for applied
mechanics in Zheleznogorsk.
</P>
<P>
The Molnia 1T was the 280th satellite put into orbit by the
Molnia M and the 260th booster used by Russia since it was put
into operation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
