<DOCNO> XIE19970925.0169 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping Theory Listed on School Schedule </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Beijing University, one of
China's most prestigious universities, has opened a course on Deng
Xiaoping Theory for its four-year students.
</P>
<P>
Twelve scholars were invited to be lecturers, including Wu
Shuqing, former president of the University and a professor of
economics; Xiao Weiyun, a law professor and a member of the
committee drafting the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
The University had finished all the preparatory work for
opening the course on Deng Xiaoping Theory before the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) opened on
September 12.
</P>
<P>
Zhao Cunsheng, vice-secretary of the CPC committee of the
university, said that the 12 professors are all experts on Deng
Xiaoping Theory and have extensive teaching experience. They will
lecture on 12 topics that cover the main contents of Deng Xiaoping
Theory.
</P>
<P>
The course is designed to help students understand that Deng
Xiaoping Theory is the Marxism of modern China and represents a
new stage of the development of Marxism in China. Students will
also study what socialism is and how to build it, the essence of
socialism and the basic rules of socialist construction.
</P>
<P>
The university has also allocated 500,000 yuan (60,000 US
dollars) to support Marxism and Leninism research on campus.
</P>
<P>
Zhao said that professors will teach the course on Deng
Xiaoping Theory by closely combining theory with actual
practice. Students have shown a strong interest in the course.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai-based Fudan University took the lead among all other
colleges and universities in China in offering such a
course. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
