<HEADLINE> Li Peng's Warnings "Timely": Indian Press </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 25 (Xinhua) -- India's economic daily The
Observer in an editorial today praised Chinese Premier Li Peng's
speech Tuesday at the opening ceremony of the World Bank and
International Monetary Fund (IMF) annual meeting held in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng's warnings to the industrial countries against their
unhelpful attitude toward the developing countries have been
"timely", the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Asia, as Li Peng pointed out, is the growth center of the world
and the industrial countries should not treat it lightly, the
editorial said, adding that Li Peng has sought active
participations of the rich in the development of the poor and has
advised the industrial countries to keep their markets open.
</P>
<P>
There is no room for threats and trade sanctions by the rich
against any poor country on pretexts like dumping when the lives
of millions are involved in the export industries of the poor
nations, it stressed.
</P>
<P>
The editorial said that Li Peng has pointed out that "the
prosperity and affluence of a small number of countries on the
basis of poverty and backwardness of the majority cannot last."
</P>
<P>
"Li Peng is also right that under no circumstances should the
industrial world impose its ideology or its social system on
others," it concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
