<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Falling Population Growth Rate for Shanxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, September 25 (Xinhua) -- A survey for the first six
months of this year revealed that the total population of north
China's Shanxi Province remained below 31.45 million.
</P>
<P>
The province recorded 194,000 births during the period, with
the birth rate dropping by 0.048 percentage points on the 1996
period.
</P>
<P>
The natural population growth rate approached three per
thousand in the province, with a total population of 31.14 million
last year. During the first six months of this year, the local
population increased by some 93,000 people.
</P>
<P>
The expected 487,000 births for the year will raise the total
population by 310,000 people.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that the province's year-end total population
will remain under 31.45 million, according to experts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
