<HEADLINE> Boca Juniors Beaten by Colo Colo in Supercup Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Diego Maradona was
substitued at halftime as Boca Juniors went down 1-2 to Colo Colo
of Chile in the South American Supercup on Wednesday here.
</P>
<P>
Maradona, playing outside Argentina for the first time since he
failed the drug test recently, didn't find his form during the
first half of the group one game.
</P>
<P>
Though Maradona played uninspired performance, the two teams
played to a 1-1 tie at halftime.
</P>
<P>
Forward Marcelo Espina opened the scorings for the home team in
the 37th minute while the Argentine side pulled back through
Mexican Luis Hernandez, who was making his debut for the team,
just one minute later.
</P>
<P>
Colo Colo, pumped up by a partisan crowd of 50,000, went on to
win 2-1 thanks to a late goal by former Chilean intenational
striker Ivo Basay.
</P>
<P>
With the victory, Colo Colo topped group one with nine points
from three games but will play their three remaining matches away
from home.
</P>
<P>
In the other matches of the day, Brazil's Vasco da Gama was
hammered by River Plate 1-5 in Buenos Aires in Group three.
</P>
<P>
River Plate was ahead in the standings with nine points,
followed by Vasco da Gama, at four.
</P>
<P>
Penarol of Uruguay was held to a 2-2 tie by Estudiants of
Argentina in Montevideo in a Group four match.
</P>
<P>
Only the group winners qualify for the semi-finals of the
competition, which is played every year between past winners of
the Libertadores Cup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
