<HEADLINE> South Korea Slams Japan-U.S. Defense Cooperation Guidelines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, September 25 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's ruling New Korea
Party (NKP) has expressed deep concern over the modified
Japan-U.S. Defense Cooperation Guidelines, saying that it has
paved the way for Japan to become a military power.
</P>
<P>
Deputy spokesman for the NKP said Wednesday the fact that the
guidelines had expanded the scope of Japan-U.S. defense
cooperation to cover the whole of the Asia-Pacific region would
invite rebuff from those neighboring countries subjected to
Japanese aggression during World War Two.
</P>
<P>
He said the guidelines was a link in the U.S. global strategy
of defense, but with the development of the situation in this
region, it might turn out to be the cause of new hegemonism of the
two countries and Japan's military expansion.
</P>
<P>
He said South Korea is following the developments very closely.
</P>
<P>
South Korea's Oriental Daily News also published a commentary
today, saying that Japan and the U.S. must take into account the
concern of the neighboring countries over the guidelines, and that
Japan must not use the guidelines as a pretext to embark on the
road of militarism.  
</P>
</TEXT>
