<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China National Day Celebrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Culture has
announced that a number of highly rated performances will be
staged in Beijing, the Chinese capital, to celebrate National Day
on October 1.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has organized a major evening theatrical
performance in the Great Hall of the People to praise the
country's flourishing economy and look forward to continuing
prosperity in the next century.
</P>
<P>
Major art troupes will stage ballet, drama, Western Opera and
traditional Beijing Opera performances during the
festival. Various repertories will highlight the 15th National
Congress of the Chinese Communist Party and the return of Hong
Kong to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
National Day will provide local artists with a rare opportunity
to exhibit their talents in the Chinese capital. One of the most
popular events is expected to be a Shanghai Children's Theater
production of a drama about Deng Xiaoping's childhood.
</P>
<P>
"The Qiong Flower Fairy", the most expensive puppet show in the
country with production costs of one million yuan (120,000 US
dollars), will premiere in Beijing. The artists from Yangzhou,
China's "Home of Puppets" in east China's Jiangsu province, have
prepared the show for four years.
</P>
<P>
A number of enthusiastic artists from the eastern province of
Shangdong will stage a local Lu Opera entitled "The Beijing Opera
for Shandong Natives". The troupe expressed the hope that staging
the opera during National Day holiday will promote a nationwide
understanding of Shangdong culture.
</P>
<P>
Artists from Russia, Germany and Israel will also stage
performances to further enhance the festive air in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
"Jiang Zemin's remarks that socialist modernization should
include both a flourishing economy and flourishing culture have
greatly inspired Chinese artists who believe that cultural
undertakings will witness further prosperity," according to a
ministry spokeswoman.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
