<HEADLINE> Disease-resistant Bean Bred in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 25 (Xinhua) -- A commercial breeding
project of a small brown Mbeya bean which resists two of the most
dreaded diseases worldwide has started in Arusha, northern
Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The breeders are now trying to transfer the resistance in the
bean to a more popular purple variety known as Kablanketi (small
blanket), sources at the Tanzania Nutrition and Food Center was
quoted by local press today.
</P>
<P>
So far, only one such resistant bean has been discovered in
the world, in El Salvador, Latin America, where it is widely bred
for commercial purposes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
