<HEADLINE> S. Africa, Togo to Promote Military Coop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 25 (Xinhua) -- South Africa and Togo
have pledged to have military cooperation, local daily "The Star"
reported today.
</P>
<P>
A far-reaching memorandum of understanding in regard to
defense cooperation between the two countries was signed in
Pretoria on Monday by South African Defense Minister Joe Modise
and his Togolese counterpart Bitokotipou Yagninim.
</P>
<P>
