<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Technique Preserves RH Negative Blood Longer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Blood Center has
introduced a new international technique which can help prolong
the preservation period of RH negative blood from 21 days to two
years.
</P>
<P>
RH negative is a rare blood type. Only three to five people per
thousand have this type of blood. Patients with RH negative blood
should receive the same during transfusions, because it has a
special antigen.
</P>
<P>
Since hospitals had difficulty preserving the blood for a long
period, they usually asked RH negative blood donors to give blood
for storage in case of emergency, or made urgent pleas through the
mass media for suitable donors.
</P>
<P>
Such ways of collecting blood are both unpredictable and
inadequate for Shanghai's need of 150,000 ml of RH negative blood
a year, doctors at the center said.
</P>
<P>
The new technique may help ease the difficulty in obtaining
blood for urgently-needed transfusions and forge closer links
between blood donation and clinical use of blood, experts said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970925.0195 </DOCNO>
