<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Opposition Enforces Countrywide Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The main opposition Bangladesh
Nationalist Party (BNP) today observed a dawn-to-dusk general
strike across the country in protest against government repression
on political rivals and ban on street rallies and processions.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Monday, the opposition on the same plea enforced a
12-hour general strike in the capital of Dhaka, which was observed
peacefully barring some stray incidents.
