broke all pledges given to the people while it was busy protecting
the interests of their masters who helped them assume power.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the ruling party's workers have been instructed by
the party high command "not to leave city streets to others for
unruly activists."
</P>
<P>
At least 117 persons were injured and many others arrested on
Wednesday when the pro and anti-strike activists clashed in
different parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Today's general strike will be the fifth by the opposition BNP
against the 15-month-old government of Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina, the arch rival of Khaleda Zia for the last six years.
</P>
