<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Diplomatic Ties with China Could Benefit Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Panama would derive a
great deal of benefit from establishing a diplomatic relationship
with China, a Panamanian economist said today.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Panama-American, a local newspaper,
Chairman of the National Research Center of the Panama University
Juan Jovane said that China occupies a decisive position nowadays
in the international community.
</P>
<P>
This can be demonstrated by China's economic growth and its
role as a permanent member of the U.N. Security Council, Jovane
said.
</P>
<P>
He said every country should accept the fact; otherwise there
is no way to discuss international relations.
</P>
<P>
Panama currently has no diplomatic relations with China. But
Jovane said China would play a crucial role in Panama's future
foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics reveal that of the five billion
U.S. dollars worth of imports registered by the Colon Free Zone
during the first six months this year, 1.3 billion dollars were
from China's Hong Kong Special Administration Region.
</P>
<P>
Jovane also pointed out that it was unwise for some countries
to maintain "diplomatic relations" with Taiwan for merely
immediate interest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
