<HEADLINE> ADB to Give 100 Million US Dollar Loan to India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) is expected to provide India with a credit of 100 million
U.S. dollars to India's Housing and Urban Development Corporation
(HUDCO), a government official said here today.
</P>
<P>
The loan, which will have a tenure of 25 years, will be
sanctioned at the next Board meeting of the Bank.
</P>
<P>
In an attempt to encourage private participation in the
construction of roads, bridges and development of other areas,
HUDCO has decided to cut the interest rate from 18 to 16 percent.
</P>
<P>
In its housing schemes, HUDCO has also effected a one percent
interest cut.  
</P>
</TEXT>
