<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. to Fund Russia's Agricultural Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The United States will provide
10 million U.S. dollars to fund Russia's agricultural sector, the
Interfax news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Vice President Albert Gore announced the plan in the
Russian city of Samara, where the Russia-U.S. Economic and
Technological Cooperation Commission was holding its ninth meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Samara region is to receive most of the money.
</P>
<P>
Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin said energy storage,
programs of converting Russian military enterprises to civilian
production and ecology are the region's key fields to be covered
by the U.S. investment.
</P>
<P>
Setting up an effective fund allocation mechanism is important
for the bilateral economic cooperation, he added.
</P>
<P>
As for Russia's bid for membership of the World Trade
Organization (WTO), Gore said it is just a question of time.
</P>
<P>
Gore and Chernomyrdin are co-chairmen of the cooperation
commission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
