<HEADLINE> Yugoslav Bank Savings Surge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavian people's bank
savings have jumped to 175 million dinars (about 29.2 million
U.S. dollars) from 94 million dinars (15.6 million U.S. dollars)
earlier this year, said the National Bank of Yugoslavia today.
</P>
<P>
People here attributed the surge to the economic recovery as a
result of the United Nations' removal of economic sanctions
against the country in October last year.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rate stood at 3 percent in the first eight months
of this year. People's average wages rose 15 percent in July from
the same month last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
