<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fuzhou Emerges as Popular Site for Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city had approved the establishment of 5,127 foreign-funded
businesses by the end of August, with related contracts involving
the use of 13.2 billion U.S. dollars in foreign investment and
actual allocations 4.9 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-funded enterprises have emerged as a major factor
contributing to the city's economic development. Last year alone,
foreign-funded enterprises contributed two thirds of the city's
total industrial output value for enterprises above the township
level.
</P>
<P>
The city's investment environment has witnessed continued
improvement since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
Fuzhou was formally named as the site for construction of
"experimental zone for agricultural cooperation across the Taiwan
Straits" in July. The city, which has also been authorized to
pilot direct shipping services, has either completed or
commissioned a group of major infrastructure projects, including
the Changle International Airport.
</P>
<P>
Fuzhou attended the recent China Investment and Trade Fair in
Xiamen, a port city of Fujian Province, and signed contracts for
252 projects involving foreign funding of 1.51 billion
U.S. dollars.. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
