<DOCNO> XIE19970925.0229 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Energy Company Reports Profit Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Eni, an Italian energy and
chemicals holding company, received net profits of 2.6 trillion
lire (about 1.5 billion U.S. dollars) in the first half of this
year, a 9.3 percent jump over the same period last year, the
company announced today.
</P>
<P>
The company's operating profits reached 447 billion lire (256
million dollars) after an 8.6 percent growth, while sales
increased 6.2 percent to 30.8 trillion lire (17.6 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
Increased sales were attributed to higher prices for petroleum
products, larger sales of crude oil and increased business in the
engineering and service sector.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Eni's net debt was nearly halved, falling to 282
billion lire (161 million dollars), thanks to a cut in interest
rates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
