<HEADLINE> Floods Leave 14,000 People Homeless in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Floods in the south of Sri
Lanka have devastated several areas and left 14,000 people
homeless, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
In Matara District, Southern province, 14,000 people have been
marooned by the floods caused by torrential rains which began
lashing the region on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
It's reported that a large number of houses have been damaged
and over 100 roads in the district are totally impassable.
</P>
<P>
There have been no reports of deaths so far.
</P>
<P>
A vast area of paddy fields have gone under water, the reports
added.
</P>
<P>
The local government is rescuing those trapped in the floods
and providing meals and dry rations to those affected.  
</P>
</TEXT>
