<HEADLINE> Finland Extends Aid to DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Finland will extend five
million Finnish marks (about 950,000 U.S. dollars) in aid to the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), the Foreign Ministry
said today.
</P>
<P>
Half of the money will be at the disposal of the World Food
Program, while the other half will be channeled through Finland's
Red Cross Society.
</P>
<P>
The Finnish government, the Red Cross Society and other
non-governmental organizations have extended a total of one
million Finnish marks (about 190,000 dollars) as emergency aid to
the DPRK since last spring.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, DPRK will be the focus of this year's "Famine Day"
donation. The activity organized by the Red Cross Society will
start on October 25. 
</P>
