<HEADLINE> Meat Fair to Help Push China's Meat Industry to New Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese meat market is
large and has great potential, and extensive international
cooperation is needed to push the meat industry to a new stage of
development, said a senior Chinese official Wednesday at the world
meat congress in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Meat production in China has grown faster than anywhere else
in the world. Both production and consumption in China make up
one-fourth of the world's total, with an annual output of 58
million tons last year, said He Jihai, vice-minister of internal
trade, at the special China topic session Wednesday afternoon.
The three-day World Meat Conference which will be closed today.
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged that projected growing demand and increased
rate of consumption in the future will mean great potential and
new opportunities for foreign capital in trade, processing and
technology cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"The meat industry has been a major area of foreign investment
since economic reforms were launched, and the level of foreign
capital utilization has been improved," the vice-minister said.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics indicate that about 1,000 joint ventures or
solely foreign funded meat processing enterprises have been set up
around the country, involving more than 2,000 cooperation projects
with 200-odd Chinese companies being registered as meat export
businesses.
</P>
<P>
In conjunction with the world meat conference, "Meat+Tec
China '97" opened at the World Trade Center in Beijing Wednesday.
The four-day specialized meat show for both the poultry and red
meat processing industries will provide Chinese meat processors
with a very good chance to communicate with such international
companies as Tetra-Laval Food, W.R. Grace, Unisono and Stork. More
than 20,000 specialists were expected to visit the show.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
