<HEADLINE> Health Education Program to Be Launched in Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- A Hong Kong charity
organization and the Yunnan provincial government will jointly launch
a health education program in rural areas of the southwest China
province.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Salvation Army and the Yunnan provincial government
plan to spend 1.5 million yuan over the next 18 months to spread
health information among rural residents and build a number of
public toilets in villages in six counties.
</P>
<P>
At least nine million farmers in Yunnan, or over 30 percent of
its total rural population, have no access to standard sanitary
toilets, officials with the Provincial Health Department said,
saying an unsanitary living environment is a "hotbed" of
infectious and parasitic diseases.
</P>
<P>
A program has also been organized to train specialized
personnel for the project.
</P>
<P>
The Salvation Army has initiated some charity activities to
provide relief for Yunnan people affected by strong earthquakes in
the past several years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
