<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Casagrande Unscathed from Car Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Francesco Casagrande, who is
expected to captain Italy's team at next month's world cycling
championships, emerged unscathed from a car crash in Florence on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Casagrande was travelling in a Fiat Marea with his Saeco team's
sporting director Franco Chioccioli and masseur Gabriele Mugnaini
when it slowed down for road works and was rammed from behind by
a lorry.
</P>
<P>
Chioccioli, who won the Tour of Italy cycling in 1991, was
taken to hospital with minor head injuries and whiplash -- having
been hit by Casagrande's bicycle which was in the back of the
estate car. He was later discharged.
</P>
<P>
Despite the accident, Casagrande will still ride in Thursday's
45th edition of the Coppa Sabatini in Florence in Tuscany at
Peccioli. 
</P>
</TEXT>
