<HEADLINE> URGENT: World Bank President Calls for Action </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 25 (Xinhua) -- World Bank President James
Wolfensohn today called on all member countries to take immediate
action to tackle pressing economic and social issues.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the closing session of the World Bank and
International Monetary Fund (IMF) annual meetings here this
morning, Wolfensohn said: "Let's not wait, let's try to focus on
the issues now."
