<HEADLINE> Former Albanian Ruling Party Leaders Sentence Reviewed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Albanian Court of Last
Instance is expected to review the guilty verdict meted out to
three former members of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the now defunct Albanian Party of Labor and to
possibly change the sentence to not guilty.
</P>
<P>
Local newspapers today reported that Foto Cami, Prokop Murra
and Muho Asllani, members of the political bureau, were expected
to re-enter a plea of not guilty as the Court of Last Instance
began to review their cases Tuesday. Prosecutors contend the men
had not committed crimes, because no such laws existed to cover
the charges they were accused of at the time.
</P>
<P>
The new hearing was the second one this week over the party's
former officials since the Labor Party, which has turned
Socialists, came to power in June after defeating the Democrats in
general elections.
</P>
<P>
The three men are accused of committing crimes of genocide and
crimes against mankind while they were in power. They were
previously sentenced to life imprisonment and imprisonment of 5-20
years by the Appeal Court.
</P>
<P>
A new court verdict on the three former officials is expected
to be decided by September 29. 
</P>
