<HEADLINE> Venezuela's Non-Traditional Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela's non-traditional
exports rose 16.5 percent in the first eight months to 3.1 billion
dollars over the same period of 1996, the Central Office for
Statistics and Information reported.
</P>
<P>
Non-traditional exports included ordinary metals, agricultural
products, foodstuffs, beverages and tobacco.
</P>
<P>
The private sector made up 75 percent of the total export volume
while the public sector accounted for 25 percent.
</P>
<P>
The office said that 51 percent of Venezuelan goods were
exported to Colombia, the United States and Japan. 
