<HEADLINE> Famine, Cholera Kill 265 in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Starvation and cholera,
caused by drought in Indonesia's Irian Jaya province, claimed 265
lives over the past few weeks, Antara news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted the Ministry of Home Affairs as saying that
254 deaths were reported in the hinterland regency of Jayawijaya
and 11 others in southeastern regency of Merauke.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports cited cholera and other drought-induced
diseases and a food shortage as causing the deaths in the
province.
</P>
<P>
In Jayawijaya, about 80,000 hectares of forest are now ablaze.
The ensuing haze has made it difficult for the local government to
help the victims, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
However, the Irian Jaya provincial administration said food and
medicine supplies have got through to some areas of Jayawijaya,
Merauke and surrounding areas.  
</P>
