<HEADLINE> Traffic Accidents, Fire Kill 551 in Lithuania This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Traffic accidents and fires
killed 551 people in Lithuania during the first eight months of
this year, reports from the Lithuanian capital of Vilnius said
today.
</P>
<P>
Figures from the Lithuanian Statistics Bureau show that 424
deaths among the total were caused by traffic accidents, up 18
percent from the same period last year. Only 127 deaths by fire
were reported, a decrease compared with that last year.
</P>
<P>
According to an Interfax news agency report, there were 3,250
traffic accidents and 7,800 fires in the former Soviet country so
far this year.
</P>
<P>
Lithuania is a country with a population of 3.7 million
people. 
</P>
