<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Second Seed Henman Out in Toulouse Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Britain's world number 20 Tim
Henman was beaten 4-6, 7-6 (3-7), 6-2 on Wednesday night by
Germany's 70th ranked Nicolas Kiefer in the second round of the
400,000-U.S.-Dollar ATP tournament in Toulouse.
</P>
<P>
Kiefer, who had already hammered Henman in a challenger event
in 1995, became too tough and left no room for the second
seed. Henman, who also had a hard first-round match against Czech
Daniel Vacek, could not afford the fierce shots from his rival.
</P>
<P>
Henman had some chances with his base-line ball in the second
set, but he didn't keep his momentum and did not break Kiefer's
serve after 2-all.
</P>
<P>
Henman said after the match that kiefer played a very good
match, especially he was good in the serve. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
