<HEADLINE> Island Hunting Club in Each China Attracts Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, September 25 (Xinhua) -- China's first island hunting
club offers visitors plenty of cool sea breezes and 13 hunting
grounds full of wild animals.
</P>
<P>
Located in east China's coastal Zhejiang province, the Nanfang
Hunting Club has received more than 4,000 visitors from both at
home and abroad since it opened last February.
</P>
<P>
Last year, hunters bagged a total of 150,000 ducks, 20,000
rabbits and 6,000 pigs.
</P>
<P>
The club is owned by the Nanfang Corp., the largest company for
wild animal raising in the province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
