<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Premier Li Peng and Kazakh President Nursultan
Abishevich Nazarbayev held talks at Alma-ata Wednesday, pledging
joint efforts to further bilateral relations, particularly
economic and trade co-operation.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Li Lanqing also arrived at Alma-ata earlier
Wednesday from Beijing to be present at the talks.
</P>
<P>
-- A campaign to study documents of the 15th National Congress
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) has been started in central
government departments. Party members and officials agree that
taking Deng Xiaoping Theory as the guiding ideology is the will
and common aspiration of the Party and the people.
</P>
<P>
-- Foreign Ministry spokesman Shen Guofang said defense
cooperation between Japan and the United States, a bilateral
arrangement formed under certain historical circumstances, should
be strictly limited within the bilateral scope in order to prevent
arousing unrest amongst Asian nations and bringing unnecessarily
complicated factors to the regional security situation.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- The Standing Committee of the Eighth National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC),
China's consultative body, ended its 22nd meeting Wednesday by
approving a resolution on studying and implementing the documents
of the 15th CPC National Party Congress.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen told a
news conference on Tuesday evening in New York that President
Jiang Zemin's visit to the United States this autumn will boost
Sino-US relations to a new stage of development.
</P>
<P>
-- The '97 Chengdu International Giant Panda Festival is being
held from September 24 to 28 to inform the Chinese people of the
indispensable relationship between man and nature and seek further
international co-operation in the protection of the giant panda.
</P>
