<HEADLINE> Spain Reaches France World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Spain gained a 2-1 win over
Slovakia in a World Cup qualifier in Bratislava, Slovakia on
Wednesday, securing a place in next year's World Cup finals in
France.
</P>
<P>
Kiko Narvaez connected with a cross of Alfonzo Perez to put
Spain into the lead in the 47th minutes.
</P>
<P>
Slovakia, with no real chance of qualifying, equalised through
Jozef Majoros in the 75th minute but Spain hit back immediately. A
76th-minute goal by Guillermo Amor ensured the Spanird's victory.
</P>
<P>
Spain, 23 points from nine matches, lead the group six followed
by Yugoslavia with 20 pionts. Even if Spain somehow managed to
lose their final game at home to the Faroe Islands and Yugoslavia
thrashed Malta, Spain would still go through as Europe's best
second-placed team.  
</P>
</TEXT>
