<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Popularizes Use of New Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The popularization of new
technology in China is playing an important role in improving
the economy and the competitiveness of businesses, according to
the State Economic and Trade Commission.
</P>
<P>
Industrial enterprises are now the biggest shoppers in China's
hi-tech market. In 1996, they purchased 18.88 billion yuan worth
of technology, 66.7 percent of which was by large and medium-sized
State-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
They also earned 4.43 billion yuan from the sale of technology.
</P>
<P>
Part of the government's technology drive is helping
enterprises utilize electronic, energy-saving, and pollution control
technology.
</P>
<P>
Some 280 high technology development pilot projects have been
set up since 1994 with 900 million yuan of special central
government loans, 210 million yuan from the State, and 3 billion
yuan from enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Government offices in charge of the spread of technology are
giving full support to 500,000 companies that do a quarter of the
technology business in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
