<HEADLINE> Romario Returns to Spain After Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian striker Romario
arrived back in Valencia on Wednesday after five weeks of
treatment in his home country and said he hoped to play against
Real Madrid this weekend.
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old Romario tore an abductor muscle on August 22
playing in a pre-season friendly for Valencia against his former
club Flamengo.
</P>
<P>
The return of the 1994 World Cup sensation will be a boost to
Valencia who have not won a point from their first three games in
the first division.
</P>
<P>
Last week the club sacked their Argentine coach Jorge
Valdano. The new coach is Claudio Rainieri, the former Fiorentina
coach.
</P>
<P>
Romario said he had not spoken to Rainieri before his arrival
in Spain and had no idea about the new coach's plans. 
</P>
