<HEADLINE> Italian Tax Revenue Rises 5.8 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Italy's tax revenue increased
5.8 percent to 314 trillion lire (about 179 billion U.S. dollars)
in the first seven months of this year over the same period last
year, said the Finance Ministry today.
</P>
<P>
Revenue rose two percent and value-added tax jumped 9.1 percent
In July over the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
The trend demonstrates that the effects of the country's
economic recovery are beginning to show in tax revenue. 
</P>
