<HEADLINE> Romania to Continue Anti-Corruption Fight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu told reporters here today that his country will
continue its fight against corruption.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu made the remarks at a press conference after
chairing a meeting of the National Council on Action against
Corruption and Organized Crimes on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Numerous crimes have threatened Romania's national security,"
said the president, stressing that the fight against corruption
will be continued to the end. He also asked the Romanian people to
cooperate with the government on the issue.
</P>
<P>
Justice Minister Valeriu Stoica told reporters that Romania
will further improve its laws and mechanisms so as to provide a
sound basis for the anti-corruption campaign.
</P>
<P>
On September 14, Constantinescu said that he will restructure
the national council. He also criticized the local anti-corruption
councils for their inefficiency. 
</P>
