<HEADLINE> Forest Rangers Busy with Animal Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Forest rangers in southwest
China's Yunnan province recently apprehended a seven-member
criminal gang which killed several wild elephants last May, and
confiscated large amounts of weapons.
</P>
<P>
Forest rangers, a new group of specialized police, were
organized two years ago in Xishuangbanna to protect the
world-renowned kingdom of wildlife in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
These animal guardians have assisted the management bureau of
the local nature reserve and the public security bureau in the
capture of 83 poachers.
</P>
<P>
Sources said Xishuangbanna now has one-fourth of the country's
mammal species and one third of the bird species. Some 109
endangered species of animals are on the list for State
protection.  
</P>
</TEXT>
