<DOCNO> XIE19970925.0273 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Firearm Law Reduces Armed Crime Incidence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The number of crimes
involving guns decreased drastically during the first five months
of this year thanks to the effective implementation of the Arms
Control Law, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Between January and May, the number of crimes involving
firearms was 48.3 percent less then in the same period last year,
said Yuan Shaoli, deputy director of the Public Order Bureau under
the Ministry of Public Security.
</P>
<P>
During the first five months, the number of murders committed
with guns dropped 37.1 percent, armed robberies 51.5 percent and
armed rapes 59.1 percent from the corresponding period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
The Arms control Law, which took effect last October, defines
over 20 types of crimes involving firearms and corresponding
punishments, which range up to the death penalty.
</P>
<P>
Punishments are much harsher and the right to bear arms
considerably more restricted under this law than the Management
Measures on Arms Control, promulgated by the State Council in 1981.
</P>
<P>
He stated that more than 80,000 small-calibre guns, 150,000
shotguns and 10,000 steel ball guns owned illegally were
confiscated in a nationwide firearms management and control
campaign in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Over 800 underground firearms' manufacturing and trafficking
centres were banned, Yuan said.
</P>
<P>
The promulgation of the strict Arms Control Law has
successfully curbed the rising tide of crimes involving guns, Yuan
said.
</P>
<P>
However, he suggested, the way each country works separately is
insufficient to deal with the increasingly serious problem of
cross-border firearms trafficking and related smuggling cases.
</P>
<P>
International co-operation should be strengthened to combat
crimes involving funs effectively, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
