<HEADLINE> Georgia Beats Moldova 1-0 in European World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Georgia won its second World
Cup qualifier on Wednesday, beating Moldova 1-0 in Kishinev,
Moldova.
</P>
<P>
Temur Ketsbaya scored the game's only goal nine minutes into
the match. He pushed the ball into the net from inside the penalty
area after it was centered by Archil Arveladze.
</P>
<P>
Moldovans responded with dozen of attacks and dominated the
first half but they failed to beat the Georgian defense.
</P>
<P>
The best chances for the home squad came in the 51st and 78th
minutes when Moldovans Serghei Rogaciov and Ion Testimiteanu had
good opportunities to score. However, their strikes were diverted
by Georgian goalkeeper Nika Togonidze.
</P>
<P>
Moldova's Alexandru Curteanu and Georgia's Georgy Kinkladze and
Kakha Kaladze were both sent off by the referee in the second
half.
</P>
<P>
Georgia and Moldova are both ranked at the bottom of Group two
and have no chance to qualify for the next year's World Cup in
France. 
</P>
</TEXT>
