<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Binhai New Area in North China City Booms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The Binhai New Area in the
north China port city of Tianjin has attracted a total contracted
foreign investment of over six billion US dollars for over 2,500
projects since 1994.
</P>
<P>
More than 150 transnational corporations, including Motorola,
Samsung and Novo Nordisk, have established metallurgical, electronics
information processing, biotechnological and food processing
enterprises in Binhai, north China's largest open area.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investment and domestic funding have contributed
greatly to the rapid development of Binhai, which
recorded an economic growth rate of 30 percent in the first half of
this year. The area's 18.1 billion yuan GDP accounted for over 30
percent of the city's total, with its total trade volume hitting
one billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Major projects under construction include a seamless steel tube
project to be completed at a cost 10 billion yuan, and a
large-scale ethylene project with an annual production capacity
of 200,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Binhai has recorded annual economic growth of 27 percent or
more for three consecutive years.
</P>
<P>
Binhai includes the Tianjin Economic Development Area, the
Tianjin Bonded Zone and the Tanggu Oceanic Hi-Tech Development
Zone. Construction of the area is scheduled for completion in
2004. 
</P>
</TEXT>
