<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uruguay to Auction Treasure From Wrecked Galleon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, September 24 (Xinhua) -- More than 150 gold and
silver coins rescued from a Spanish galleon wrecked in Rio de La
Plata in 1752 will be auctioned here in October.
</P>
<P>
The auction will also include silver indian heads, cannons,
bullets, shells and anchors from the ship "Nuestra Senora de la
Luz" ("Our Lady of Light").
</P>
<P>
Ruben Collado, the Argentine owner of the ancient pieces,
started searching for the galleon in 1991 and discovered treasures
worth 4 million U.S. dollars from the wreckage.
</P>
<P>
The money from the auction will belong to Collado to support
his continued search for the poop and cabin of the ancient ship.
</P>
<P>
The gold and silver coins were minted in 1749, 1750 and 1751 at
the Chilean National Mint. 
</P>
</TEXT>
