<HEADLINE> AT&AMP;T to Buy Stake in Italian Telecommunications Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. telecommunications
company AT&AMP;T announced Wednesday that it will buy 1.2 percent
stake in the Italian telecommunications giant Telecom Italia when
the latter is privatized.
</P>
<P>
In exchange, Telecom Italia will purchase stock worth the same
amount in the U.S. company.
</P>
<P>
The purchase of the 1.2 percent stake will give the AT&AMP;T a seat
in the Telecom Italia board of directors.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement announced on July 2, the two companies will
also launch a joint venture in Latin America and Telecom Italia
will join AT&AMP;T's European telecom consortium Unisource. 
</P>
</TEXT>
