<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil to Receive More Investment on Power Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Investments on
electric power in Brazil surpassed 15 billion U.S. dollars over
the last five years.
</P>
<P>
In the next 5 years, 30 billion dollars will be invested in
the energy sector of Brazil, stated Peter Greiner, the secretary
general of the Ministry of Mines and Energy, at an International
Conference titled "Operating Electric Systems in a Competitive
Environment", held in Curitiba, Parana state`s capital.
</P>
<P>
Projects with these investments will provide more than 22,000
megawatts of power to the electric network by the year 2002, with
a 4,400-megawatt-a-year growth, making sure the needed supply for
the country, according to Greiner.
</P>
<P>
The current growing rate of the electric market is 5 percent a
year, which demands to build new hydroelectric plants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
