<HEADLINE> Moya and Corretja Beaten in Romanian Open Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Carlos Moya and
Alex Corretja of Spain were both eliminated out of the
475,000-U.S.-Dollar Romanian Open tennis tournament here on
Wednesdsay.
</P>
<P>
The two main upset were produced by two all-spaniard
second-round matches.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Moya went down to Carlos Costa 0-6, 6-4, 4-6 while Alex
Corretja lost to Javier Sanchez 3-6, 6-4, 5-7.
</P>
<P>
Moya, ranked 5 by the ATP, played poorly in the first set. He
seemed to recover in the second set when he broke Costa's serve
once, but his 87th ranked opponent prevailed in the last set.
</P>
<P>
The ninth-ranked Corretja and 58th-ranked Sanchez played a
balanced first two sets.
</P>
<P>
The match's main moment came in the third set at 6-5 for
Sanchez. Corretja waited too long to serve. German referee Roland
Herfer granted a point to his opponent as a penalty for time
violation.
</P>
<P>
The decision affected Corretja's concentration. He lost another
point and double faulted to forfeit the match.
</P>
<P>
In two other second-round matches, Mark Kevin Goellner of
Germany beat Norway's Christian Ruud 6-2, 5-7, 6-3, while Spaniard
Francisco Clavet defeated Tomas Behrend of Germany 7-6 (7-5),
6-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
