<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bulgaria's Soccer Club Dobrich Punsihed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian first division soccer
club Dobrudzha Dobrich were on Wednesday fined 736,000
U.S. dollars and banned from playing league games at home until
the end of the year after their players abandoned a game earlier
this month.
</P>
<P>
Dobrudzha club president Stefan Kolev ordered his players off
the pitch in the 62nd minute of the September 13 game against
Lokomotiv Sofia, saying he feared for the safety of the referee
after Lokomotiv took a 2-0 lead and Dobrudzha captain Emil
Mitsanski was shown a red card.
</P>
<P>
The punishment was handed out by the Bulgarian football union,
who separately fined Kolev 680,000 U.S. dollars for his actions.
Mitsanski was banned for four games and given a smaller
fine. Another player was fined and banned for two games.
</P>
<P>
The football union last week awarded Lokomotiv Sofia a 5-0
away win, placing them fifth in the league table. 
</P>
</TEXT>
