<HEADLINE> Sampras Advances to Quarters in Grand Slam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Pete Sampras of the
United States outplayed Spaniard Felix Mantilla 6-4, 3-6, 6-2 to
advance to the quarter-finals of the six million U.S. dollars
Grand Slam Cup tennis tournament in Munich on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Sampras lost the second set due to a pair of consecutive double
faults, but recovered to eliminate Mantilla in 90 minutes by
winning the third set with an unreachable backhand.
</P>
<P>
As a result, Sampras will meet Jonas Bjorkman of Sweden, who
beat defending champion Boris Becker 6-3, 6-2, in the
quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Both Sampras and Bjorkman were instrumental in guiding their
nations into next month's Davis Cup final, to be played in
Gothenburg, Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Sampras and Bjorkman will play Friday, as will Briton Greg
Rusedski and Russian Yevgeny Kafelnikov. 
</P>
</TEXT>
