<HEADLINE> Output of Major Machinery Products In Mixed Change </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics from
State Statistical Bureau show that the output of major machinery
products changed mixedly during the January-July period.
</P>
<P>
The country manufactured power generating equipment with nine
million kw in power generating capacity, up 7.6 percent over the
same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The output of alternate motors stood at 29.6 million kw, up 5.8
percent.
</P>
<P>
However, the output of metal-cutting machines was 89,100 sets,
down 5.1 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
