<HEADLINE> China Expands High-Yielding Soybean Crop Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The land in China
used for a type of high-yielding soybean, the "Hefeng 25", has been
increased to one million ha, and output is going up by 1.65
billion kg.
</P>
<P>
This means a two billion yuan increase in profits.
</P>
<P>
The Hefeng 25 was developed by Liu Zhongtang, the director of
the State Soybean Engineering Technology Research Center. It has
an average yield of 2,250 kg per ha and more than twice that at
its highest, a higher yield than the best American or Japanese
varieties.
</P>
<P>
Since the mid-1980s, China has accelerated the use of the
Hefeng 25, extending its use to Heilongjiang and Jilin provinces
in the northeast and the Inner Mongolia Region in the
north. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
