<HEADLINE> China's Automobile Output Changed Mixedly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- China manufactured 980,000
automobiles during the first seven months of this year, up 7.7
percent over the same period in 1996, according to the latest
statistics from State Statistical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China made 54,371.9 large tractors, up 8.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
The country also produced 1.1 million small tractors, down 9.6
percent.  
</P>
