<HEADLINE> Venezuela Calls for Clearance of U.N. Dues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela today called
on those states which owe membership dues to the United Nations to
clear their debts without condition.
</P>
<P>
"It is essential that the member states pay their contributions
on time," Foreign Minister Miguel Angel told the on-going 52-nd
session of the U.N. General Assembly here.
</P>
<P>
He said no country can refuse to honor the accepted obligation
or set conditions, as such conditions "represent a threat to the
equality of the states and the dignity of the world forum of which
we are a part."
</P>
<P>
Regarding the U.N. reform, he said an increase of the number of
permanent members in the Security Council should "be based on the
ultimate interests of the international community, including fair
distribution for all geographical regions."
</P>
<P>
He said Venezuela hopes that the upcoming special U.N. General
Assembly on drug trafficking to be held at the request of Mexico
will produce clear solutions ensuring a more successful battle
against drug trafficking. 
</P>
</TEXT>
