<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bonn to Decide on Eurofighter Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The German government will make
a decision on October 8 on whether to join Britain, Italy and
Spain to build a new-generation of fighter jets, called the
Eurofighter, for the next century, German Defense Minister Volker
Ruehe announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Due to tight budgets induced mainly by its struggle to meet the
strict fiscal requirements for joining the single European
currency, the Bonn government has delayed a decision on the
Eurofighter project for several times.
</P>
<P>
The German Defense Ministry said that it was absolutely
necessary for the German air force to buy 180 Eurofighters to
replace the outdated Phantom jets currently in service. The
purchases are expected to cost Germany about 23 billion marks.
</P>
<P>
Although Germany's participation in the project is expected to
be approved by the government eventually, the strong opposition
from the opposition Social Democratic Party (SPD) and the Greens
will make it relatively difficult to get an endorsement from the
German parliament, observers said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
