<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian Shows Concern for Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- China is showing its
concern for the deadlocked peace process in the Middle East,
Chinese Foreign Minister Qian Qichen told Jordan Foreign Minister
Fayez Tarawneh here today.
</P>
<P>
During their talks, Qian said that relevant resolutions of the
United States should be respected. The principle of "land for
peace" should be maintained, he said. Countries in the Middle East
should share security and stability.
</P>
<P>
He also told the Jordan foreign minister that China appreciated
the consistent efforts of Jordan in propelling the Middle East
peace process.
</P>
<P>
While reviewing the bilateral relations, Qian said that there
has been great progress in the goodwill cooperation since the two
countries set up diplomatic links 20 years ago. China has been
consistent in supporting the just cause of maintaining state
sovereignty and land integrity of the Jordan people, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qian also said he appreciated the Jordan government, which,
in the Taiwan issue, understands the feeling of the Chinese people
and is for the policy of "One China."  
</P>
</TEXT>
